{
    "Info": [
        {
            "title": "How to Create a Simple Ruby on Rails App",
            "desc": "Explains how to create a simple Ruby on Rails frontend and Rest Api",
            "ref": "ruby-on-rails"
        }
    ],
    "Instructions": [
        {
            "id": 1,
            "instruction": "A lot of this information comes from this [video](https://youtu.be/2DvrRadXwWY?si=zxWyo6DvhYWBTdZf)."
        },
        {
            "id": 2,
            "instruction": "Ruby is our programming language, Rails is the framework, and Sqlite3 will be our database."
        },
        {
            "id": 3,
            "instruction": "Before we start make sure you have homebrew installed. If the first command doesn't output a version, run the second command.",
            "Code": {
                "Name": "",
                "Description": "",
                "Language": "Command",
                "FormatCode": "brew --version\n/bin/bash -c \"$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/HEAD/install.sh)\"",
                "CopyCode": "brew --version\n/bin/bash -c \"$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/HEAD/install.sh)\""
            }
        },
        {
            "id": 4,
            "instruction": "Install rbenv on your computer. For this example use Homebrew to install it.",
            "Code": {
                "Name": "",
                "Description": "",
                "Language": "Command",
                "FormatCode": "brew install rbenv",
                "CopyCode": "brew install rbenv"
            }
        },
        {
            "id": 5,
            "instruction": "Run this command to initialize rbenv in your ~/.zshrc file.",
            "Code": {
                "Name": "",
                "Description": "",
                "Language": "Command",
                "FormatCode": "echo 'if which rbenv > /dev/null; then eval \"$(rbenv init -)\"; fi' >> ~/.zshrc",
                "CopyCode": "echo 'if which rbenv > /dev/null; then eval \"$(rbenv init -)\"; fi' >> ~/.zshrc"
            }
        },
        {
            "id": 6,
            "instruction": "Reload the zsh configuration to apply your changes using the following command.",
            "Code": {
                "Name": "",
                "Description": "",
                "Language": "Command",
                "FormatCode": "source ~/.zshrc",
                "CopyCode": "source ~/.zshrc"
            }
        },
        {
            "id": 7,
            "instruction": "Close your terminal. Then open a new one and run the following command to ensure rbenv is installed right. If the commands output has rbenv in it somewhere, you should be good",
            "Code": {
                "Name": "",
                "Description": "",
                "Language": "Command",
                "FormatCode": "brew search rbenv",
                "CopyCode": "brew search rbenv"
            }
        },
        {
            "id": 8,
            "instruction": "Now install Ruby 3.2.2 using rbenv. This will probably take roughly 5 minutes. I'd recommend setting a timer.",
            "Code": {
                "Name": "",
                "Description": "",
                "Language": "Command",
                "FormatCode": "rbenv install 3.2.2",
                "CopyCode": "rbenv install 3.2.2"
            }
        },
        {
            "id": 9,
            "instruction": "Set the global rbenv to use Ruby 3.2.2 using the following command.",
            "Code": {
                "Name": "",
                "Description": "",
                "Language": "Command",
                "FormatCode": "rbenv global 3.2.2",
                "CopyCode": "rbenv global 3.2.2"
            }
        },
        {
            "id": 10,
            "instruction": "Now close your terminal and open a new one. In the terminal run the following command. The output should say \"ruby 3.2.2\" at the beginning.",
            "Code": {
                "Name": "",
                "Description": "",
                "Language": "Command",
                "FormatCode": "ruby -v",
                "CopyCode": "ruby -v"
            }
        },
        {
            "id": 11,
            "instruction": "Now install rails. This will probably take roughly 2-5 minutes. I've included the V (verbose) flag so you can see the progress of the download and the API calls that are being made.",
            "Code": {
                "Name": "",
                "Description": "",
                "Language": "Command",
                "FormatCode": "gem install -V rails",
                "CopyCode": "gem install -V rails"
            }
        },
        {
            "id": 12,
            "instruction": "After you've done that close your terminal and open a new one. Run the following command to ensure rails was installed correctly.",
            "Code": {
                "Name": "",
                "Description": "",
                "Language": "Command",
                "FormatCode": "rails -v",
                "CopyCode": "rails -v"
            }
        },
        {
            "id": 13,
            "instruction": "The sqlite3 database engine should come preinstalled on mac. However I'd still recommend downloading it via Homebrew to update the version.",
            "Code": {
                "Name": "",
                "Description": "",
                "Language": "Command",
                "FormatCode": "brew install sqlite",
                "CopyCode": "brew install sqlite"
            }
        },
        {
            "id": 14,
            "instruction": "Now ensure you have all your programs installed properly. These commands should all output a version.",
            "Code": {
                "Name": "",
                "Description": "",
                "Language": "Command",
                "FormatCode": "ruby -v\nrails -v\nsqlite3 --version",
                "CopyCode": "ruby -v\nrails -v\nsqlite3 --version"
            }
        },
        {
            "id": 15,
            "instruction": "After you've successfully downloaded all those three programs, we can start working on our project."
        },
        {
            "id": 16,
            "instruction": "I've always liked the school website \"Canvas\" UI and I saw it was originally built in Ruby on Rails. So for nostalgia purposes I'll be recreating the dashboard in these instructions."
        },
        {
            "id": 17,
            "instruction": "Create your new project using the following command. This might take a minute. It will initialize an empty git repository. Commit the initial template code. There's no remote repo to push to.",
            "Code": {
                "Name": "",
                "Description": "",
                "Language": "Command",
                "FormatCode": "rails new canvas-example\ncd canvas-example\ngit add .\ngit commit -m \"Initial Commit\"",
                "CopyCode": "rails new canvas-example\ncd canvas-example\ngit add .\ngit commit -m \"Initial Commit\""
            }
        },
